metadata.name: Wooded Solitude #110
metadata.description:
"Wooded Solitude" is an exploration of my love for crystals, architecture, being one with nature, escaping technology and becoming ok with the idea of being alone. The series was derived using diffusion Ai models and put together in a generative image composition on fx(hash). 

May 2022
150 editions were made available.

metadata.name: Trillingen #79
metadata.description:
Trillingen is the next evolution of the Familiar Relations project. It is a visual representation of the knowledge, beauty, and pain that vibrates from one generation to the next. 

- Press [ r ] to change circle and outline colors
- Press [ s ] to save image to disk as a .png

Made with p5js.

metadata.name: Rain Ritual #142
metadata.description:
Every windy gust.... every breeze, gave the restless grasses a chance to spread their suggestive rumours, their spurious gossip. All the while, Old Ones of the field towered above, chanting to their wrathful Sky God for more rain.... Always more rain. 

Instructions 
Intended for high resolutions. Use the following keys once render is complete, to export (letters export without a border) 

Square mode 
   1 (q) : 2048x2048  
   2 (w) : 3072x3072 
   3 (e) : 4096x4096 
   4 (r) : 5120x5120 

Landscape mode (increases spacing between objects to preserve aspect ratio) 
   5 (t) : 2560x1440 
   6 (y) : 3840x2160 
   7 (u) : 5128x2880 
   8 (I) : 7680x4320 

Note: Generated textures are resolution dependant, resulting in very slight differences across resolutions. Composition however, remains identical. 

Browsers 
Tested with Chrome, Edge and Firefox on Windows, Chrome on Mac. 
Note for Firefox users : Ensure "Use hardware acceleration" is ticked – Found in Settings / Performance. Other advanced settings to enable include : gfx.canvas.accelerated,  gfx.direct2d.force-enabled and gfx.offscreencanvas.enabled - Unfortunately even with these, Firefox appears slower than other browsers.  

Shoulders of Giants [license text and links included in source] 
- Aristid Lindenmayer – Formal L-System language (Tree routine) 
- P5.js - Creative coding framework 
- JS Topology Suite "JSTS", a port of Java Topology Suite "JTS" - High-level Geometry library 

Additional JS functions 
- Epistemex - Cardinal Splines library (Curve calculations) 
- MaetDol - K-Means library (Tree foliage routine) 
- Angelos Chalaris - Directed Graphs Tutorial (Tree routine)

metadata.name: pollocian fibs #85
metadata.description:
This generative token is based on Fibonacci words in a 3D dimensional space, enhanced with Perlin noise.

* Press "s" to save the current image
* Press "h" to stop the animation
* Press "r" to resume the animation

Feature:
* color scheme: 17 variations of sets of 4 colours
* start angle: first direction, between 0 and 360
* step: determines the distance between dots, between 15 and 45
* angle: the angle of each turn, between 85 and 95
* width: determines the size of the dot. Between 1 and 10.
* dots: the number of dots for each cycle
* frames: number of frames before animation stops
* noise seed: seed for perlin noise function

metadata.name: Bézier Bloom #40
metadata.description:
When spring doesn't come soon enough, we can make our own spring. Branch by branch, petal by petal, watch a tree come into being and bloom.

Controls:
"a": toggle between animation and final drawing.
"i": toggle day/night (invert colors).
"p": pause/resume animation.
"s": save image.
A tree grows different during the day and at night. You can become a master of time to nurture your own unique tree.

These interactive drawings are made entirely of Bézier curves.
Created by Elsif (ElsifThen@twitter) using p5js.

metadata.name: Liquid Cubes #51
metadata.description:
A series of rotating, ever-changing, quasi-liquid cubes.

Variables:
There are 7 different color palettes, resulting in many more color schemes since the colors (from one palette) get shuffled for each mint.
The sides of a big cubes have between 5 and 10 small cubes (or spheres).
There are a zillion patterns being generated for the small cubes.
The spheres can be shiny or matte.

Interactivity:
Use the mouse to rotate them and to zoom in and out.
Press the arrow_up and arrow_down keys to change the speed of the artwork
Press ‘s’ to save the current frame as a PNG.

metadata.name: Ten #7

Ten colors, ten palettes, ten styles. "Ten" is a collection of mathematical illustrations, combining techniques I have explored in past projects with my latest experiments.

Press [s] to save the image in 4096x4096 resolution.

By Roni Block (@BlockRoni)
